<graph edgedefault="directed"><node id="&quot;COMMUNISTES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A French political faction on the left end of the political spectrum, mentioned as part of the arc that needs to be mobilized for national effort."&lt;SEP&gt;"The communists are a French political group mentioned as part of the political spectrum that needs to be mobilized for a national effort."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-61659a768934b7ee8b99c4caa2dc73f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2f7aa0930a810d99a7277de4db2ec96f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DETTE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Debt is a central economic concept in the text, specifically France's national debt. The discussion debates its sustainability, the consequences of cancellation, and its impact on the country's financial credibility."&lt;SEP&gt;"Debt is a critical category described as the hidden financier of social benefits, with the text revealing that the last three days of each month's pension payments are funded by debt."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Debt is a major economic problem discussed, with a stated need to find 120 billion euros in savings per year just to stabilize it."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c40155ff1959faacc40ac81a1bd82732&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d0c7252335013b007b44502aab156b75&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a6c18fd60d725c0dd2b48e489b44a89</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ARTICLE 49.3&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A constitutional mechanism used by the French government to pass the budget without a full parliamentary vote."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-de1e838c4a16c8ea8dfe127a589137ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PIERRE BOURDIEU&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A sociologist whose school of thought is blamed by Dufourcq for promoting an ideology that designates an enemy (liberals) to justify expanding individual rights."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-14e4b66af7e240a6e454da971c593ede</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RAYMOND BARRE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Former French Prime Minister who created a 10% tax abatement for retirees in 1977."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c0fa7905a87ac3fcff901f5c962535c9</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;KEYNÉSIANISME&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Keynesian economics; the economic theory that Dufourcq argues France has actually embraced to an extreme degree."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-14e4b66af7e240a6e454da971c593ede</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MASS UNEMPLOYMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The mass unemployment that began after 1974 as a consequence of economic policies and inflation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-de1e838c4a16c8ea8dfe127a589137ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WASHINGTON&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Washington is mentioned in a quoted excerpt from Nicolas Dufourcq's book as a European capital where the French situation causes astonishment."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2f7aa0930a810d99a7277de4db2ec96f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;IMPÔT SUR LE REVENU&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The income tax is cited as a benchmark for national financial scale, with the cost of a past pension reform equated to two-thirds of its annual revenue."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5a6c18fd60d725c0dd2b48e489b44a89</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;POPULISTES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Populists represent a political category; people who are turning to populism because they feel abandoned and despised by the current system."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2f7aa0930a810d99a7277de4db2ec96f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PRODUCTIVITÉ&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Productivity is presented by Philippe Aghion as a key challenge that must be met through innovation to finance the social model."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c40155ff1959faacc40ac81a1bd82732</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ÉTAT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The French state, described as being financially depleted ('à jeun', 'nu comme un verre') and unable to fund public services without reforming pensions and healthcare."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b901d171dd5785e4ce0ac05b882d406d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RÉPLIQUES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Répliques is a radio program hosted by Alain Finkielkraut, featuring discussions on various topics with experts."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5fb2a574f750d88794cd45cf0819ffea</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RÉVOLUTION TECHNOLOGIQUE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Technological Revolution is mentioned as a global phenomenon from which a country with a good education and flexicurity system can benefit greatly."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c40155ff1959faacc40ac81a1bd82732</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COLLÈGE DE FRANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Collège de France is a prestigious higher education and research institution where Philippe Aguillon serves as professor."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-de1e838c4a16c8ea8dfe127a589137ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SOCIAL WELFARE EXPANSION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The expansion of social welfare programs in 1974-1976 including new allocations for disability, single parenthood, and elderly poverty."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-de1e838c4a16c8ea8dfe127a589137ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ÉDOUARD PHILIPPE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A former French Prime Minister cited by Finkielkraut for using a Bob Dylan quote in a policy speech."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-14e4b66af7e240a6e454da971c593ede</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RÈGLE D'OR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The 'golden rule' is a fiscal principle mentioned in the context of the Gercarco pension regime, ensuring balance and triggering automatic indexations if agreements are not met."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5a6c18fd60d725c0dd2b48e489b44a89</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;1969 CURRENCY DEVALUATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The 1969 currency devaluation decision by Georges Pompidou that triggered inflation and subsequent economic consequences."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-de1e838c4a16c8ea8dfe127a589137ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FONDATEURS DE 1945&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The founders who conceived the original French welfare state model after World War II."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-de1e838c4a16c8ea8dfe127a589137ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ALEXANDRA MALKA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Alexandra Malka is the director of the 'Répliques' radio program."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5fb2a574f750d88794cd45cf0819ffea</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HOMME DE LA RUE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The 'man on the street' is a conceptual category representing the ordinary citizen who would be astonished by the described political demagogy."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2f7aa0930a810d99a7277de4db2ec96f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FONCTION PUBLIQUE HOSPITALIÈRE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A specific branch of the French public service dealing with hospital and healthcare administration."&lt;SEP&gt;"The hospital civil service, identified as a public sector with a management culture that remains similar to the outdated practices described by Philippe Aghion."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f44f51fafa9fb2ab36dcce22ab1fd71d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d1c98cbcc5c65952fc4e69108ecc5d8</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LA BULLE COGNITIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The cognitive bubble; a shared false belief, discussed as the misconception that France has become neoliberal while the welfare state is collapsing, when the opposite is argued to be true."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-14e4b66af7e240a6e454da971c593ede</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RETRAITES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"French pension system described as overly generous and financially unsustainable, requiring reforms like raising retirement age and disindexation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pensions, the largest expenditure of the French social protection system at 410 billion euros."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-61659a768934b7ee8b99c4caa2dc73f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c0fa7905a87ac3fcff901f5c962535c9</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;APPROCHE SCHUMPETERIENNE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Schumpeterian approach is an economic philosophy referenced by the speaker, emphasizing creative destruction and the role of entrepreneurs in driving innovation and social mobility."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d0c7252335013b007b44502aab156b75</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NICHE DU TREIL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A tax loophole (niche) designed to facilitate business succession and preserve employment, but which has been abused by including non-professional assets."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b901d171dd5785e4ce0ac05b882d406d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;JEU À SOMME NULLE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Zero-sum game; a mindset described by Aghion where one party's gain is seen as another's loss, contrasted with a production-focused social democracy."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-14e4b66af7e240a6e454da971c593ede</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MIRACLE COLLECTIF&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The 'collective miracle' is a term used to describe the French welfare state and way of life, which is argued to require rules of finitude to remain sustainable."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5a6c18fd60d725c0dd2b48e489b44a89</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;YANN LEQUIN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cited as an example of someone leaving Meta to start a new AI venture, representing entrepreneurial movement in AI."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bc173c20fe16236b49dc39f9e7d15fcf</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EUROPE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Europe is a geopolitical entity portrayed as the bearer of values like freedom and democracy, which France is tasked with upholding and strengthening."&lt;SEP&gt;"Europe is referenced as a geopolitical entity experiencing technological decline compared to the United States and China."&lt;SEP&gt;"The continent and political union of which France is described as a central pillar, responsible for carrying certain values."&lt;SEP&gt;"The continent mentioned by Philippe Aghion in the context of needing to become more productive and innovative."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-14e4b66af7e240a6e454da971c593ede&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-61659a768934b7ee8b99c4caa2dc73f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c40155ff1959faacc40ac81a1bd82732&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2f7aa0930a810d99a7277de4db2ec96f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GAUCHE REDISTRIBUTIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The redistributive left is a political category focused on wealth distribution through mechanisms like taxes, which is contrasted with the speaker's productivist approach."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d0c7252335013b007b44502aab156b75</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FRANCE CULTURE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"France Culture is a French public radio channel and cultural broadcaster that produces this discussion program."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-de1e838c4a16c8ea8dfe127a589137ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MARISOL TOURAINE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Marisol Touraine is mentioned as the politician who implemented a pension reform in 2013, noted as a rare left-wing reform in this area."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d0c7252335013b007b44502aab156b75</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ÉCOLOGIE DE L'ÉTAT-PROVIDENCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Ecology of the welfare state is a concept attributed to Nicolas Dufourcq by Alain Finkielkraut, implying the need to save it through sacrifices rather than adding new rights."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c40155ff1959faacc40ac81a1bd82732</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INDIVIDUALISME DÉMOCRATIQUE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A concept from Tocqueville describing a societal trend toward personal privatization and delegation of responsibilities to the sovereign."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f44f51fafa9fb2ab36dcce22ab1fd71d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RAYMOND ARON&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Raymond Aron was a French philosopher and sociologist. He is cited by Finkielkraut for his famous question 'What would you do in his place?', a principle that guided his later work on political responsibility."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c40155ff1959faacc40ac81a1bd82732</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;35 HEURES PAYÉES 39&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The '35 heures payées 39' (35 hours paid for 39) refers to the French law that reduced the official work week to 35 hours while aiming to maintain salaries, cited as a pivotal moment that changed the French relationship with work."&lt;SEP&gt;"The '35 hours paid 39' is a policy event cited as a factor that changed the French relationship to work, anchoring a specific idea about working hours and pay."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4d1c98cbcc5c65952fc4e69108ecc5d8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a6c18fd60d725c0dd2b48e489b44a89</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RÈGLE D'ÉQUILIBRE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The 'rule of balance' is synonymous with the 'golden rule' within the Gercarco pension system, designed to maintain financial equilibrium."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5a6c18fd60d725c0dd2b48e489b44a89</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HOLDINGS PATRIMONIALES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Patrimonial holdings, a financial structure discussed as being potentially misused for personal luxury purchases instead of legitimate business purposes."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b901d171dd5785e4ce0ac05b882d406d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PENSION REFORM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pension Reform is a proposed policy change discussed by Philippe Aghion as necessary for France's future, though he suggests it should be done differently."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5fb2a574f750d88794cd45cf0819ffea</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;UNEDIC&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"French unemployment insurance organization that RSA beneficiaries are being integrated with to return to job market."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c0fa7905a87ac3fcff901f5c962535c9</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;META&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A technology company mentioned as the previous employer of Yann Lequin who left to pursue AI development."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bc173c20fe16236b49dc39f9e7d15fcf</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NÉOLIBÉRALISME&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"An economic and political ideology debated in the text, often criticized and contrasted with social democracy and the welfare state."&lt;SEP&gt;"Neoliberalism; an economic theory presented as a mischaracterization of France's actual policy direction, used as a political foil."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f44f51fafa9fb2ab36dcce22ab1fd71d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-14e4b66af7e240a6e454da971c593ede</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HORIZON&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Horizon is a political party in the Pays de la Loire region, presided over by Christelle Morencet."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5a6c18fd60d725c0dd2b48e489b44a89</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SÉBASTIEN LECORNU&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sébastien Lecornu is a French government official, mentioned in the context of being praised for his work on budget and pension reform."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c40155ff1959faacc40ac81a1bd82732</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ÉCOLE DE PHILOSOPHIE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The school of philosophy that prepared the birth of the welfare state in the early 20th century, associated with Léon Bourgeois."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-61659a768934b7ee8b99c4caa2dc73f3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MARIO DRAGHI&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"An economist and former central banker whose agenda for increasing productivity and innovation in Europe is mentioned by Philippe Aghion."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-14e4b66af7e240a6e454da971c593ede</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;L'EUROPE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Europe, referenced as a collective entity whose neighbors are used as a benchmark for France's employment rates and economic performance."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-118614beec01eb5355b255debcebf23c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MICHEL ROCARD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Former French Prime Minister involved in debates about the creation of the RMI (Revenu Minimum d'Insertion)."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c0fa7905a87ac3fcff901f5c962535c9</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SUÈDE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A country (Sweden) cited by Philippe Aghion as an example of a successful model with social mobility and innovation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Sweden is cited as a country that exemplifies social mobility and innovation, serving as a model for the speaker's economic vision."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-14e4b66af7e240a6e454da971c593ede&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d0c7252335013b007b44502aab156b75</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MORT DE DÉSESPOIR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The French term for 'death of despair,' a phenomenon of increased mortality among a specific demographic."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f44f51fafa9fb2ab36dcce22ab1fd71d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MÉLANIE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Likely refers to Giorgia Meloni, the Prime Minister of Italy, used as a counterexample to the situation in France."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-61659a768934b7ee8b99c4caa2dc73f3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SOCIAL-DÉMOCRATIE DANOISE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Danish social democracy is referenced as an example of a political movement that has voted to raise the retirement age to 67 with a perspective of 70."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5a6c18fd60d725c0dd2b48e489b44a89</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DÉSINDUSTRIALISATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Deindustrialization, a past process in France that Nicolas Dufourcq has written about previously."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2f7aa0930a810d99a7277de4db2ec96f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DROIT DE PROPRIÉTÉ&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Right to Property is a sacred concept invoked by the speaker to argue against the Zucman tax, which he frames as an attack on this fundamental right."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d0c7252335013b007b44502aab156b75</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LE TAUX D'EMPLOI DES SENIORS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The employment rate of older workers, specified as being insufficient in France and identified as one of the economic levers that need to be addressed."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-118614beec01eb5355b255debcebf23c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OLIVIER MARLEX&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A deceased individual (referred to as 'the late Olivier Marlex') who, along with Xavier Bertrand, was aligned on the pension reform issue, specifically seeing a problem with the retirement age."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-118614beec01eb5355b255debcebf23c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SOUVERAIN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A concept referring to the sovereign state or ruler to which democratic individuals delegate increasing responsibilities, potentially becoming a tutelary despot."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f44f51fafa9fb2ab36dcce22ab1fd71d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FRANÇOIS MITTERRAND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"François Mitterrand was the French President whose 1982 pension reform is cited as a costly historical policy that reduced the retirement age."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5a6c18fd60d725c0dd2b48e489b44a89</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OPINION FRANÇAISE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"French public opinion is a concept questioned by Alain Finkielkraut, asking the guests what they would do politically given its current state."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c40155ff1959faacc40ac81a1bd82732</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SECTEUR FORMEL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The formal economic sector, criticized by Nicolas Dufourcq as being disproportionately targeted for revenue generation in the 2025 budget, similar to practices in developing economies."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b901d171dd5785e4ce0ac05b882d406d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CULTURE DU MANAGEMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"This refers to the overarching category of management culture and hierarchical relationships within French companies and the public sector. It is described as problematic, with a focus on criticizing subordinates rather than praising them, and a lack of employee consultation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4d1c98cbcc5c65952fc4e69108ecc5d8</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GEORGES POMPIDOU&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Georges Pompidou was President of France who decided to devalue the currency in 1969 against Raymond Barr's advice."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-de1e838c4a16c8ea8dfe127a589137ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ANNULATION DE LA DETTE (1797)&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Cancellation of Debt in 1797 was a historical event under Minister Dominique Ramelle of the French Directory, where French public debt was partially cancelled, typically following a revolution."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c40155ff1959faacc40ac81a1bd82732</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RAPPORT AU TRAVAIL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"This category describes the changing relationship that the French have with work. Key ideas include the perception that remuneration is disconnected from work intensity, that real life begins outside of work, and that retirement is seen as a liberation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4d1c98cbcc5c65952fc4e69108ecc5d8</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SOUTIENABILITÉ&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sustainability, specifically referring to the financial sustainability of the French social model and pension system, which is a central argument for reforming them."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4d1c98cbcc5c65952fc4e69108ecc5d8</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TIERS-MONDISATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The concept of 'third-worldization' used by Nicolas Bavray to diagnose France's economic and social decline, comparing it to developing nations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b901d171dd5785e4ce0ac05b882d406d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MINISTÈRE DES AFFAIRES ÉTRANGÈRES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The French Ministry of Foreign Affairs is the institution where Raymond Aron had a meeting with an undersecretary of state during his time in Germany."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c40155ff1959faacc40ac81a1bd82732</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ÉTAT PROVIDENTIEL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"An expanded, more interventionist version of the welfare state that emerged in the 1970s under Giscard d'Estaing."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-de1e838c4a16c8ea8dfe127a589137ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DÉFAUT ARGENTIN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Argentine Default refers to the historical event where Argentina defaulted on its national debt, leading to decades of difficulty in regaining trust and access to international financial markets."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c40155ff1959faacc40ac81a1bd82732</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MODÈLE SOCIAL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The French social model, whose sustainability is a key concern. The need to balance social accounts is presented as a necessity for this model's survival."&lt;SEP&gt;"The social model is the European system of social protection and welfare that the discussants argue must be sustained through innovation and productivity."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4d1c98cbcc5c65952fc4e69108ecc5d8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c40155ff1959faacc40ac81a1bd82732</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ANNÉES 70&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The 1970s are referenced as an era characterized by a 'verticale descendante' (top-down) management culture in French companies, from which significant progress has supposedly been made."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4d1c98cbcc5c65952fc4e69108ecc5d8</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CHINE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"China is referenced as a global leader in breakthrough innovation, serving as a benchmark against which France's technological decline is measured."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c40155ff1959faacc40ac81a1bd82732</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GAULLISME&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Gaullism is a French political ideology based on the ideas of Charles de Gaulle; described here as needing modernization."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2f7aa0930a810d99a7277de4db2ec96f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RÉVOLUTION DE L'INTELLIGENCE ARTIFICIELLE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The AI revolution described as a major technological shift and source of economic growth."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bc173c20fe16236b49dc39f9e7d15fcf</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RETRAITÉS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Retirees are a demographic category whose pensions are financed by a shrinking number of active workers, creating a financial strain on the system."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5a6c18fd60d725c0dd2b48e489b44a89</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CHRISTELLE MORENCET&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Christelle Morencet is the president of the Horizon party in the Pays de la Loire region. She is cited for her comments on the changing ratio of workers to retirees and her political stance on the budget."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5a6c18fd60d725c0dd2b48e489b44a89</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LE PREMIER MINISTRE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Prime Minister of France, whose approach to passing a budget Philippe Aghion supported based on an assessment of opportunity cost and political stability."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-118614beec01eb5355b255debcebf23c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DAVOS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The World Economic Forum held in Davos, Switzerland, where Marc Carnet was reportedly formidable, indicating a key international economic meeting."&lt;SEP&gt;"The location of the World Economic Forum, mentioned as a place where European partners were anxiously waiting to see if France would pass a budget."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-61659a768934b7ee8b99c4caa2dc73f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-118614beec01eb5355b255debcebf23c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COUCHE KEYNÉSIENNE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Keynesian layer refers to an economic policy approach based on the theories of John Maynard Keynes, mentioned as one of the 'chimeras' believed to easily generate growth."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c40155ff1959faacc40ac81a1bd82732</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;XAVIER BERTRAND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A French politician who, according to Philippe Aghion, was aligned with the view that there was a problem with the retirement age during the 2023 pension reform negotiations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-118614beec01eb5355b255debcebf23c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LÉON BOURGEOIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A historical French philosopher and statesman from the early 20th century who laid the philosophical groundwork for the welfare state."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-61659a768934b7ee8b99c4caa2dc73f3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;JUSTICE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The French justice system, mentioned as another public service that has suffered from pauperization."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b901d171dd5785e4ce0ac05b882d406d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BOB DYLAN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A musician quoted by Édouard Philippe in a political speech, as mentioned by Finkielkraut."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-14e4b66af7e240a6e454da971c593ede</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ÉTAT-PROVIDENCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The French welfare state model, originally conceived in 1945 and significantly expanded in the 1970s."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Welfare State is a key social and economic model discussed. The debate centers on how to finance and sustain it through innovation and productivity, and the risks it faces from fiscal irresponsibility."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Welfare State is the central organization discussed, characterized by its vertiginous growth, bipartisan political support, and the financial challenges it presents."&lt;SEP&gt;"The welfare state is a category representing the French social model. The discussion centers on making it sustainable by accepting rules of finitude and fiscal balance."&lt;SEP&gt;"The welfare state model, characterized by state-provided social protections like unemployment insurance, healthcare, and education."&lt;SEP&gt;"The welfare state, a central concept in the discussion about France's social model, its financing, and its philosophical foundations."&lt;SEP&gt;"The welfare state, described as a miraculous and beautiful construction that is a duty to preserve and transmit to future generations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d0c7252335013b007b44502aab156b75&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2f7aa0930a810d99a7277de4db2ec96f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a6c18fd60d725c0dd2b48e489b44a89&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f44f51fafa9fb2ab36dcce22ab1fd71d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-61659a768934b7ee8b99c4caa2dc73f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c40155ff1959faacc40ac81a1bd82732&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-de1e838c4a16c8ea8dfe127a589137ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PENSION REFORM SUSPENSION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The suspension of pension reforms in France using article 49.3, which was a key marker of Macron's second term."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-de1e838c4a16c8ea8dfe127a589137ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CRÉDIT IMPORT-CHERCHE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A tax credit mechanism in France intended for innovation, but criticized for being misused and poorly targeted by some companies and individuals."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b901d171dd5785e4ce0ac05b882d406d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PHILIPPE DOUSTE-BLAZY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Philippe Douste-Blazy is identified as one of the founding fathers of the Carte Vitale, a French health insurance card, representing right-wing contributions to the welfare state."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d0c7252335013b007b44502aab156b75</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ELIE COHEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Elie Cohen is a co-author of a book on economic models and new growth ideas, mentioned by Alain Finkielkraut."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5fb2a574f750d88794cd45cf0819ffea</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BLANCHARD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Co-author of the Blanchard-Tirole report, an economic study that includes a chapter on reworking the points-based pension system, cited as a reference."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-118614beec01eb5355b255debcebf23c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SANTÉ&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Healthcare system in France facing financial challenges due to 100% reimbursement model and low out-of-pocket payments."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c0fa7905a87ac3fcff901f5c962535c9</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ACTIFS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Actives or workers are a demographic category whose ratio to retirees is cited as having drastically changed, from 4-to-1 to 1.3 or 1.5-to-1, highlighting a core problem of the pension system."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5a6c18fd60d725c0dd2b48e489b44a89</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ASSEMBLÉE NATIONALE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Assemblée nationale is the French national assembly where the debate over the pension reform took place. It is described as a place of 'invectives et des insultes' (invectives and insults) rather than constructive debate."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4d1c98cbcc5c65952fc4e69108ecc5d8</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ARRIÈRES PETITS-ENFANTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Future generations (great-grandchildren) who will bear the financial burden of current social spending."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-de1e838c4a16c8ea8dfe127a589137ac</data>
</node>
