  <data key="d1">"A needed pension reform mentioned as a necessity to free up state resources for other public services like education and security."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pension reform is a significant political event, with the text noting that most reforms have been implemented by the right wing, except for the 2013 reform by Marisol Touraine."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pension reform is a specific policy measure mentioned, for which Sébastien Lecornu received praise from Nicolas Dufourcq."&lt;SEP&gt;"The pension reform is a major political event in France. The specific reform discussed aimed to raise the retirement age to 64 and was met with significant public and political blockages, insults, and a lack of substantive debate."&lt;SEP&gt;"The pension reform is the central event and policy debate discussed throughout the text, concerning changes to the retirement age, financing, and system structure (e.g., points-based system)."</data>
