<node id="&quot;NICOLAS DUFOURCQ&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">Nicolas Dufourcq is the Director General of the Banque publique d’investissement (BPI France) and an author with approximately 30 years of experience as a business leader. He has written a book on France's "social debt" and the changing relationship of the French with work, topics he frequently discusses in economic and political debates.

In his analyses, Dufourcq argues that France is not a neoliberal state but has instead become "hyper-Keynesian," characterized by a significant and unsustainable expansion of the welfare state financed by debt. He critiques what he describes as a "cognitive bubble" surrounding this issue. Engaging in discussions on pension reform, healthcare financing, and broader economic challenges, he advocates for specific reforms to ensure the system's sustainability. These include raising the retirement age and implementing a points-based pension system.

He strongly argues against proposals like the cancellation of national debt or the implementation of a Zucman tax, citing historical precedents like the French Directory in 1797 and Argentina to emphasize the importance of fiscal responsibility. Instead, Dufourcq champions a vision for a more "productive and vital" France, where innovation and a robust productive economy are essential for sustaining an inclusive social model. He has also drawn parallels to his childhood in Africa to critique France's economic decline and has commented on the "family secret" and lie surrounding neoliberalism</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-14e4b66af7e240a6e454da971c593ede&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d1c98cbcc5c65952fc4e69108ecc5d8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-118614beec01eb5355b255debcebf23c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a6c18fd60d725c0dd2b48e489b44a89&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d0c7252335013b007b44502aab156b75&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c0fa7905a87ac3fcff901f5c962535c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b901d171dd5785e4ce0ac05b882d406d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5fb2a574f750d88794cd45cf0819ffea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2f7aa0930a810d99a7277de4db2ec96f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f44f51fafa9fb2ab36dcce22ab1fd71d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-61659a768934b7ee8b99c4caa2dc73f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c40155ff1959faacc40ac81a1bd82732&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-de1e838c4a16c8ea8dfe127a589137ac</data>
</node>
