<edge source="&quot;ALAIN FINKIELKRAUT&quot;" target="&quot;NICOLAS DUFOURCQ&quot;">
  <data key="d3">74.0</data>
  <data key="d4">"Alain Finkielkraut addresses Nicolas Dufourcq directly, asking for his opinion on the state of France's public services and a diagnosis of decline."&lt;SEP&gt;"Alain Finkielkraut concludes the program by promoting Nicolas Dufourcq's book on France's social debt."&lt;SEP&gt;"Alain Finkielkraut directly addresses Nicolas Dufourcq, asking him to explain the French blockage on pension reform and if circumventing the obstacle was necessary."&lt;SEP&gt;"Alain Finkielkraut directly addresses and questions Nicolas Dufourcq about social debt and convincing the French to make sacrifices."&lt;SEP&gt;"Alain Finkielkraut directly addresses and questions Nicolas Dufourcq, specifically about his praise for Sébastien Lecornu and his policy proposals in light of public opinion."&lt;SEP&gt;"Alain Finkielkraut engages with and quotes Nicolas Dufourcq, facilitating the discussion on pension reform and the French blockage."&lt;SEP&gt;"Alain Finkielkraut interacts with Nicolas Dufourcq, who contributes to the discussion on the 'lie' of neoliberalism."&lt;SEP&gt;"Alain Finkielkraut interviews Nicolas Dufourcq, prompting him to explain his economic views and respond to policies like the Zucman tax."&lt;SEP&gt;"Alain Finkielkraut quotes from Nicolas Dufourcq's book to support his line of questioning about French singularity and demagogy."</data>
